{
  "texts": [
    "Given this, the FCC-ee program is expected to have an enormous impact.",
    "In this context it is important to emphasize that while the U(2) 5 flavor symmetry effectively sidesteps flavor and collider bounds, it is less effective against EWPO.",
    "This is particularly true if we combine the U(2) 5 symmetry with the hypothesis of NP coupled mainly to the third generation, exploiting the inherent asymmetry between heavy and light flavors at proton-proton colliders.",
    "This asymmetry is not present in many EWPO given their sensitivity to heavy flavors, either at the tree level or via quantum effects.",
    "Given these considerations, a future EW precision machine like FCC-ee stands out as the optimal method to either confirm or refute a range of compelling NP models that are currently consistent with present data.Important progress is also expected on a shorter timescale in view of the improvements foreseen for selected flavor-violating observables."
  ]
}